w: #fff 0px 0px 5px;                          color: #444">Working with Color</div></div><div style="margin-top: 20px; background-color: #white;                        color: black;                       margin-left: 20px;                        margin-right: 20px;"><div style="position: absolute;                          left: 20px;"><a accesskey="p" href="tool-options.html">Prev</a></div><div style="position: absolute;                          right: 20px;"><a accesskey="n" href="image-effects-chapter.html">Next</a></div><div class="navCenter"> </div></div><div class="chapter" lang="en"><div class="titlepage"><div><div><h2 class="title"><a name="working-with-color"></a>Chapter 4. Working with Color</h2></div></div></div><div class="sect1" lang="en"><div class="titlepage"><div><div><h2 class="title" style="clear: both"><a name="color-box"></a>The Color Box</h2></div></div></div><p>
<span class="inlinemediaobject"><img src="color_box.png" alt="Color Box"></span>
</p><p>The Color Box has 3 main sections: the Color Tablet, the Color Palette
and the Color Similarity Selector.</p><p>The Color Tablet shows the current foreground color as a square on top
of another square representing the current background color. When drawing
with the <span class="mousebutton">left</span> mouse button, the foreground color is used, and when drawing with the
<span class="mousebutton">right</span> mouse button the background color is used (except for the <a href="tool-erasers.html" title="Erasers">Erasers</a>).  You can click on the double-ended
arrow to swap the foreground and background colors.  </p><p>The Color Palette shows a selection of colors for you to choose
from. The translucent pyramid represents the transparent color. Left-click
on a color to set the foreground color and right-click on a color to set the
background color. You can also drag and drop any opaque color into the Color
Tablet squares. To edit a color in the Color Tablet or Palette, double-click
on it. The <a href="tool-color-picker.html" title="Color Picker 
">Color Picker</a> tool allows
you to select a color from the image.  </p><p>Color Similarity allows you to work more effectively with dithered
images and photos. It applies to transparent selections, as well as the
<a href="tool-flood-fill.html" title="Flood Fill

">Flood Fill</a>, <a href="tool-erasers.html#tool-eraser-clr" title="Color Eraser

">Color Eraser</a> and <a href="image-autocrop.html" title="Autocrop / Remove Internal Border">Autocrop / Remove Internal Border</a> tools. Double-click on the Color
Similarity Selector to choose how similar colors must be to be considered
identical. When using selections in Transparent mode, any color in the
selection that is similar to the background color will also be made
transparent.</p></div></div><div style="background-color: #white; color: black;                  margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px;                  margin-right: 20px;"><div style="position: absolute; left: 20px;"><a accesskey="p" href="tool-options.html">Prev</a></div><div style="position: absolute; right: 20px;"><a accesskey="n" href="image-effects-chapter.html">Next</a></div><div align="center"><a accesskey="h" href="index.html">Home</a></div></div><div style="background-color: #white;   color: black;         margin-left: 20px;   margin-right: 20px;"><div class="navLeft">Common Tool Options </div><div class="navRight"> Image Effects</div><div class="navCenter"><a accesskey="u" href="index.html">Up</a></div></div><br><br><div class="bannerBottom" style="background-image: url(bottom-middle.png);                                        background-repeat: x-repeat;                                         width: 100%;                                         height: 100px;                                         bottom:0px;"><div class="BannerBottomRight"><img src="bottom-right.png" style="margin: 0px" alt=""></div><div class="bannerBottomLeft"><img src="bottom-left.png" style="margin: 0px;" alt=""></div></div></body></html></FILENAME><FILENAME filename="image-effects-chapter.html"><html><head><title>Chapter 5. Image Effects</title><link rel="stylesheet" href="kde-default.css" type="text/css"><meta name="generator" content="DocBook XSL Stylesheets V1.67.2"><meta name="keywords" content="kolourpaint, kdegraphics"><link rel="start" href="index.html" title="The KolourPaint Handbook"><link rel="up" href="index.html" title="The KolourPaint Handbook"><link rel="prev" href="working-with-color.html" title="Chapter 4. Working with Color"><link rel="next" href="image-autocrop.html" title="Autocrop / Remove Internal Border"><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8"><meta name="GENERATOR" content="KDE XSL Stylesheet V1.13 using libxslt"></head><body bgco